article.headline: E. Kentucky 68, Morehead St. 47
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. -- Glenn Cosey scored a game-high 17 points for Eastern Kentucky as it beat Morehead State 68-47 in an Ohio Valley Conference game Saturday night. Eric Stutz had 12 points and Corey Walden added 11, helping Eastern Kentucky (19-6, 8-3) win its third straight game. Morehead State (11-14, 5-6) shot just 21.7 percent (5 of 23) in the first half and trailed at halftime 30-20. The Colonels shot 60.9 percent (14 of 23) in the second half to extend their lead, and led by as many 24 points. Eastern Kentucky outscored the Eagles 38-10 in the paint and had a 24-4 advantage on points off turnovers. No player had over four rebounds for Morehead State, as the Colonels were outrebounded 32-24. Angelo Warner scored 16 points and Bakari Turner was the only other player for Morehead State in double figures with 10.
